{"round":1,"task":"Write a Rust function to reverse a string.","worker_output":"# Reverse a String in Rust\n\nHere's a complete implementation with multiple approaches and tests:\n\n```rust\nfn reverse_string(s: &str) -> String {\n    s.chars().rev().collect()\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let examples = vec![\n        \"Hello, World!\",\n        \"Rust\",\n        \"\",\n        \"a\",\n        \"racecar\",\n        \"Hello, 世界\",     // Unicode characters\n        \"café\",            // Multi-byte characters\n    ];\n\n    for s in examples {\n        println!(\"Original : {:?}\", s);\n        println!(\"Reversed : {:?}\", reverse_string(s));\n        println!();\n    }\n}\n\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_basic_string() {\n        assert_eq!(reverse_string(\"Hello\"), \"olleH\");\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_empty_string() {\n        assert_eq!(reverse_string(\"\"), \"\");\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_single_char() {\n        assert_eq!(reverse_string(\"a\"), \"a\");\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_palindrome() {\n        assert_eq!(reverse_string(\"racecar\"), \"racecar\");\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_with_spaces() {\n        assert_eq!(reverse_string(\"Hello World\"), \"dlroW olleH\");\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_unicode() {\n        assert_eq!(reverse_string(\"Hello, 世界\"), \"界世 ,olleH\");\n    }\n\n    #[test]\n    fn test_numbers() {\n        assert_eq!(reverse_string(\"12345\"), \"54321\");\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## How It Works\n\n```\ns.chars()           →  Iterator over Unicode scalar values (chars)\n         .rev()     →  Reverses the iterator\n               .collect() →  Collects chars back into a String\n```\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n| Choice | Reason |\n|--------|--------|\n| `&str` input | Accepts both `&str` and `String` (via `Deref`) |\n| `.chars()` | Correctly handles Unicode — iterates over **characters**, not bytes |\n| `.rev()` | Lazy reversal — no extra allocation for the reversed iterator |\n| `.collect::<String>()` | Efficiently builds the result string |\n\n## Why Not Use Bytes?\n\n```rust\n// ❌ WRONG — breaks multi-byte Unicode characters\nfn reverse_bytes(s: &str) -> String {\n    let reversed: Vec<u8> = s.bytes().rev().collect();\n    String::from_utf8(reversed).unwrap() // May panic on Unicode!\n}\n\n// ✅ CORRECT — works with all Unicode\nfn reverse_string(s: &str) -> String {\n    s.chars().rev().collect()\n}\n```\n\nRun the tests with:\n```bash\ncargo test\n```","ratings":[{"model":"claude-3-5-haiku:0","signal":true,"prediction":0.85,"rbts_score":1.0715338160159513,"payout":0.9875503542463752,"balance_after":99.98755035424638},{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5:0","signal":true,"prediction":0.92,"rbts_score":1.1037338159879515,"payout":1.0574385331230047,"balance_after":100.057438533123},{"model":"claude-sonnet-4:0","signal":true,"prediction":0.92,"rbts_score":1.1037338159879515,"payout":1.0574385331230047,"balance_after":100.057438533123},{"model":"claude-3-7-sonnet:0","signal":true,"prediction":0.97,"rbts_score":1.1147338159679514,"payout":1.081313376815975,"balance_after":100.08131337681597},{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6:0","signal":true,"prediction":0.92,"rbts_score":1.1037338159879515,"payout":1.0574385331230047,"balance_after":100.057438533123},{"model":"gpt-4o-mini:0","signal":true,"prediction":0.75,"rbts_score":0.9915338160559513,"payout":0.8139151271595247,"balance_after":99.81391512715952},{"model":"gpt-4o:0","signal":true,"prediction":0.95,"rbts_score":1.1115338159759511,"payout":1.0743679677463913,"balance_after":100.0743679677464},{"model":"gpt-4.1:0","signal":true,"prediction":0.95,"rbts_score":1.1115338159759511,"payout":1.0743679677463913,"balance_after":100.0743679677464},{"model":"gpt-4.1-nano:0","signal":true,"prediction":0.75,"rbts_score":0.9915338160559513,"payout":0.8139151271595247,"balance_after":99.81391512715952},{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5:0","signal":true,"prediction":0.95,"rbts_score":1.1115338159759511,"payout"